(a) the representations and warranties of the Borrower set forth in this Agreement and in the other Loan Documents shall be true and correct (or, in the case of the representations and warranties in Sections 3.03, 3.05 and 3.14 of this Agreement, and in Section 2.03 of the Guarantee and Security Agreement, true and correct in all material respects) on and as of the date of such Loan or the date of issuance, amendment, renewal or extension of such Letter of Credit, as applicable, or, as to any such representation or warranty that refers to a specific date, as of such specific date;
 
(b) at the time of and immediately after giving effect to such Loan or the issuance, amendment, renewal or extension of such Letter of Credit, as applicable, no Default shall have occurred and be continuing;
 
(c) either (i) the aggregate Covered Debt Amount (after giving effect to such extension of credit) shall not exceed the Borrowing Base reflected on the Borrowing Base Certificate most recently delivered to the Administrative Agent or (ii) the Borrower shall have delivered an updated Borrowing Base Certificate demonstrating that the Covered Debt Amount (after giving effect to such extension of credit) shall not exceed the Borrowing Base after giving effect to such extension of credit as well as any concurrent acquisitions of Portfolio Investments or payment of outstanding Loans or Permitted Indebtedness; and
 
(d) to the extent that, after giving effect thereto, the aggregate Revolving Credit Exposure would exceed $750,000,000, the Borrower shall have delivered to the Administrative Agent (i) a resolution of the Board of Directors of the Borrower authorizing the incurrence of indebtedness hereunder up to an amount not less than $800,000,000, which resolution has been duly certified by an officer of the Borrower, and (ii) an opinion of Maryland counsel to the Borrower to the effect that the incurrence of indebtedness in such amount has been duly authorized by all necessary corporate or other action on the part of the Borrower, each of which certification and opinion shall be reasonably satisfactory to the Administrative Agent.
 
