"" means any Indebtedness of the Borrower (which may be Guaranteed by Subsidiary Guarantors) that (a) has no amortization prior to, and a final maturity date not earlier than, six months after the Termination Date, (b) is incurred pursuant to documentation containing other terms (including interest, amortization, covenants and events of default) and, in each case, no more restrictive in any material respect upon the Borrower and its Subsidiaries than those set forth in this Agreement and (c) is not secured by any assets of any Obligor.
