(a) . Unless previously terminated, the Commitments of each Class shall terminate on the Commitment Termination Date.
Scheduled Termination
applicable
(b) . The Borrower may at any time terminate, or from time to time reduce, the Commitments of Class; that (i) each reduction of the Commitments of a Class shall be in an amount that is $25,000,000 or a larger multiple of $5,000,000 in excess thereof and (ii) the Borrower shall not terminate or reduce the Commitments of Class if, after giving effect to any concurrent prepayment of the Syndicated Loans of such Class in accordance with Section 2.10, the total Revolving Credit Exposures of such Class would exceed the total Commitments of such Class.
