SECTION 2.19. . The Borrower agrees to pay to the Administrative Agent for account of each Class B Dollar Lender, each Class B Multicurrency Lender and each Class C Multicurrency Lender an extension fee, which shall accrue at a rate per annum equal to 0.30% on the average daily unused amount of the Class B Dollar Commitment, the Class B Multicurrency Commitment and the Class C Multicurrency Commitment, as applicable, of such Lender during the period from and including the Amendment No. 1 Effective Date to but excluding the Class A Termination Date and shall accrue at a rate per annum equal to 0.50% on the daily average unused amount of the Class B Dollar Commitment, the Class B Multicurrency Commitment and the Class C Multicurrency Commitment, as applicable, of such Lender during the period from and including the Class A Termination Date to but excluding the earlier of (i) the date such Commitment terminates and (ii) the Class B Termination Date and the Class C Termination Date, as applicable. Accrued extension fees shall be payable within one Business Day after each Quarterly Date and on the earlier of (i) the date the Commitments of the respective Class terminate and (ii) the Class B Termination Date and the Class C Termination Date, as applicable, commencing on the first such date to occur after the date hereof; that all accrued extension fees shall be paid on the Class A Termination Date. All extension fees shall be computed on the basis of a year of 360 days and shall be payable for the actual number of days elapsed (including the first day but excluding the last day). For purposes of computing extension fees of the Class B Multicurrency Lenders, the Class B Multicurrency Commitment shall be deemed to be used to the extent of the outstanding Syndicated Loans and LC Exposure of such Class B Multicurrency Lender (and the Swingline Exposure of such Class of such Class B Multicurrency Lender shall be disregarded for such purpose). All extension fees payable under this Section 2.19 shall be paid on the dates due, in Dollars and immediately available funds, to the Administrative Agent for distribution to the Class B Dollar Lenders, the Class B Multicurrency Lenders and the Class C Multicurrency Lenders, as applicable. Fees paid shall not be refundable under any circumstances absent obvious error.
