Opined-on Law
Based upon the foregoing and subject to the limitations, qualifications, exceptions and assumptions set forth herein, we are of the opinion that:
1. Assuming the Notes are duly authenticated by the Trustee and issued and delivered by the Company against payment therefor in accordance with the terms of the Underwriting Agreement, the Indenture and the Second Supplemental Indenture, the Notes will constitute valid and binding obligations of the Company, entitled to the benefits of the Indenture and the Second Supplemental Indenture and enforceable against the Company in accordance with their terms.
